article.headline: McHenry's 22 lead Western Kentucky over Middle Tennessee 88-65

images.name: Babacar Faye gets up for the nice dunk for Western Kentucky
images.caption: Babacar Faye gets up for the nice dunk for Western Kentucky

article.linkText: McHenry's 22 lead Western Kentucky over Middle Tennessee 88-65
article.story: BOWLING GREEN, Ky. -- — Don McHenry's 22 points helped Western Kentucky defeat Middle Tennessee 88-65 on Saturday night. McHenry was 7-of-13 shooting, including 5 for 6 from 3-point range, and went 3 for 4 from the foul line for the Hilltoppers (15-7, 4-4 Conference USA). Rodney Howard added 16 points while going 6 of 13 and 4 of 6 from the free-throw line, and he also had five rebounds. Tyrone Marshall shot 5 for 9, including 0 for 3 from beyond the arc to finish with 12 points. The Blue Raiders (8-14, 2-5) were led in scoring by Jalen Jordan, who finished with 22 points. Jestin Porter added 18 points, seven rebounds and four assists for Middle Tennessee. Elias King also had eight points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
